						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in the Ānjanēyasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>10th-11th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 10th-11th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Damaged and portion of the text written in Telugu verse. Registers, the gift of 50 <hi rend="italic">maruturs</hi> of land by certain Namena peggaḍa got renovated the temple, probably erected by Agasti (Agasthya). It also records on the second side to the value of <hi rend="italic">Dharma</hi> and eulogises the charity of Ammenapeggaḍa.</p>						

						</summary>
